4 Quick Tips to Master Your Push Ups🌟💫

This is one movement that takes time to master, but once you do it truly is one of the best exercises because it activates your entire anterior chain of the body. 

Here are a couple of steps you can start with to progress up….

1️⃣ Kneeling Push Ups - This is the best way for beginners to learn how to recruit all of the right muscles and build up initial strength to handle their own body weight. Start in a prone position laying flat on your belly. Place your hands down in line with your shoulders, activate your glutes, engage your core and press up forming a nice long line from head, shoulder hips to knees. As you inhale, lower your body down forming a 90 degree angle at your elbow, exhale press away. Repeat! 

2️⃣ One leg Push Ups - This is a great way to build up the strength to do a full push up. This is a unilateral movement which means one side of the body is working while the other side is forced to stabilize. It adds more weight load, while still forcing you to recruit your core muscles to avoid rotation and shift in weight distribution. Both sides are forced to work independently of each other. Start out doing 6 on each side and progress as you perfect your form. 

3️⃣ Superman Push Ups - This is a great way to train your body to work in both the concentric and eccentric phase to aid in getting full range of motion. It also adds the extra bonus of activating the posterior chain of the body.

4️⃣ Full Push Ups - Start in one long dart position with your head reaching away from your tailbone. As you inhale lower the body down evenly forming a 90 degree angle at the shoulder, elbow and wrist, then exhale extend the arms back to your plank. Repeat!!

“Knee Health: Tips and Tricks for Keeping Your Joints Strong and Flexible”

Truth be told, as we get older the impact on our joints takes a toll - unless you are taking care of your body the right way. 

Some things to ask yourself….

1. Are you working the surrounding muscles of your joints?

2. Are you wearing the right shoes for the right style of training? This will affect your alignment and help/hinder muscle imbalances.

3. Are you mixing up your workout routine? Adding in strength, cardio, Pilates and proper stretching to maintain flexibility and mobility in the joints?

4. Are you making the time to warm up properly aka rolling out and cooling down with your static stretches after every workout?

5. Are you following a progressive program that builds a strong foundation so that your body adapts over time? 

All of this interplays on your joint health. 

To get you started today try adding in these three variations of glute exercises to your workout routine to fire the intrinsic muscles around your pelvis and spine. You may be surprised when you feel muscles you have never felt before or muscles that simply have not been used in quite some time. 

Not only do these types of exercises target your glutes and abductors, but they also elongate the hip flexors for those who spend excessive amounts of time sitting all day. 

The key is to mix it up and keep the body moving - body longevity is always the goal!

Why You Should Follow Progressive Programming! 🌟

Are you ready to take your workouts to the next level? 💪🏋️‍♀️ Progressive programming is the secret sauce to maximize your results, prevent overtraining, build strength and muscle, enhance skill development, and promote long-term sustainability. 🚀✨
And….I am going to tell you why! 

1️⃣ Maximizes Results: Say goodbye to plateaus! With progressive programming, your workouts continuously challenge your body, pushing you to new levels of strength, endurance, and fitness. By gradually increasing the intensity, volume, or complexity of exercises over time, you’ll experience continuous progress and achieve amazing results. 

2️⃣ Prevents Overtraining: It’s all about BODY LONGEVITY! Progressive programming takes into account the principle of gradual adaptation, allowing your body to adjust and recover adequately between workouts. This approach helps prevent overtraining and reduces the risk of injuries caused by excessive strain or fatigue. Your body deserves the right balance! 

3️⃣ Builds Strength and Muscle: Progressive overload, a key component of progressive programming, stimulates muscle growth and strength gains. By gradually increasing the resistance, repetitions, or time under tension, you provide the necessary stimulus for your muscles to adapt and grow stronger. 

4️⃣ Enhances Skill Development: Progressively building upon exercises and movements allows you to improve your technique and skill level over time. By mastering the fundamentals and gradually adding complexity, you can enhance your movement patterns, coordination, and overall performance. It’s time to level up!

Truth be told there is never a “perfect time” and we won’t always be motivated. Everyone has seasons in their life and it’s working through those hard seasons, staying consistent and attaching an intrinsic motivation that will keep you going. 

Consistency turns into a habit. Habits = action! Action = results!! An object in motion stays in motion. 

It’s about showing up for yourself even when you don’t want to. It’s being where you are, trying your best and remembering how good you are going to feel afterward. 

I regret this workout said no one ever! My advice start small…. Create a foundation that you can build upon. Even if it’s 10 min everyday. It all adds up and leads to big results! 

You can do hard things! Set goals, crush them, rinse and repeat!

Action or excuses? 🚫 You can’t have both!!! 

As I always say “there is no better time to start than now!” and…… “when something is a priority to you then you “make” time.” 

Time management 🌟 

It’s not a sexy conversation and truth be told so many people don’t realize how much time they truly waste doing things that are not helpful or taking them closer to their goals. The art of distraction is a real thing and many of us are “busy” but not intentional with our time. 

How many wasted minutes do you spend a day scrolling through social media? How much time do you spend binging on Net Flix? How much time do you spend worrying about what other people are doing? 

Believe me there are times when you need to just be and recharge your battery - yes!!!! It’s balance, but I encourage you to take out a pen and paper. Yes, I am a dork like this and really dissect how you spend your time for 24-48 hours. Ask yourself is this taking me closer to my goal or further away???

How you spend your time will dictate your results. We all make time for things when they matter to us. Give us joy, fulfillment, happiness, immediate gratification, etc. 

Sometimes we have to work through the hard things aka creating new habits, patterns, breaking old ones,  trying new things to figure out what works and what does not work. It’s experimentation. It’s living your authentic life. 

If you take anything away from this post I hope it brings light to what can be/ possibility. 

Will it be easy? No! Change is hard! Stepping outside of your comfort zone is hard. However, once you cross that bridge the feeling on the other side is 💪💫⭐️😀! 

I hope you choose growth. If you need a push, a high five, a cheerleader don’t hesitate to reach out because that’s what I want for all of you.

Setting goals ➡️ accomplishing them ➡️ feeling your best!! I LOVE GOALS!!!! And…. There is no better time to set them NOW!! 

5 Habits that will help you reach your goals⭐️

1. Meal Plan - Planning ahead is key when it comes to food. We live life on the go constantly so having healthy food accessible is key to fueling properly. This will help keep your energy levels up, improve your performance, prevent blood sugar drops throughout the day and above all will save you money long term.

2. Schedule out your workouts in advance - I am a huge advocate of having a set time/schedule that is uninterrupted dedicated to your workouts. Set these as appointments with yourself that cannot be broken. 

3. Follow a plan structured work design - This is crucial! Having a set plan of action is key to seeing results. Your body’s ability to adapt over time, adding load, intensity, reps, sets, tempo all while maintaining body longevity. Miscellaneous workouts = random results! Set program = results! This is why I have made it my life’s mission to teach people how to train efficiently and effectively to see results. The @brooketaylorfitapp encompasses this and gives you 9 months of progressive training. 

4. Hydrate - make it a point to hydrate regularly to keep your cells functioning properly, regulate body temperature, lubricate the joints, sustain energy levels, deliver nutrients to the cells. 

5. Regular Sleep Schedule - maintaining a healthy sleep schedule will help you regulate your internal clock so that you get better sleep quality on a consistent basis. This will affect your mood, performance, reduce stress load and also lower your risk for developing chronic illnesses.

Have you ever watched people do specific exercises and yet you wonder why you can’t seem to tap into your glutes? 

You don’t feel the same burn as everyone else? Well there is a reason for that and most people don’t talk about it. 

It’s called …. Postural deviations and muscle imbalances! 

We are all born a certain way and over time our habits, rituals, work, kids etc interplay with how we move. For example carrying your bags on one side, holding the kids on one hip, lifting or rotating a certain way.

Truth be told if you have lordosis like me 🙋🏼‍♀️ then you may be overactive in your hip flexors which means that your glutes maybe harder to “turn on” or activate. 

I have found over the years that through muscle balance, recovery and activation that I feel stronger and more empowered than ever. This came with using mini resistance bands to specifically target the intrinsic muscles around your pelvis and core! 

Now I don’t know about you but I got sick of getting tied up in my bands which is why I created a “game changer duo” that not only hold your bands in place but avoid the pinching, gripping and pulling.
